\begin_layout Subsection*
Step One: Character Concept 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To begin creating a Luminous, come up with a rough idea of who you want
 to play.
 What kind of upbringing did she have? What kind of experiences, good or
 bad, did she have growing up? What does she think of the world around her?
 What does she want to see the world become? What has she experienced to
 lead her to want to change the world? What led up to her Blossoming, if
 it happened before the game starts?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Don't worry too much about details like Invocations yet.
 Instead, try to figure out who your character is inside, how they think
 and feel, and who they see themselves as.
 From that, distill it into a simple core concept like "young politician"
 or "aspiring writer".
 As you go through the character creation process, you can always fall back
 on this initial seed and do whatever feels right given it or adjust it
 if you think something else would fit her just a slight bit better.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
I was never really good at collapsing down my characters into an easily
 expressed high concept.
 Still, I don't know any better advice to give.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Aspirations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Finally, choose your character's Aspirations.
 Hopeful have two more aspirations than usual, for a total of five.
 Two of them must be related to the supernatural world, or her Dream Form.
 What does she want to do to make the world a better place? What supernatural
 creatures has she run into before, and what does she like to do with them?
 Has she run into any supernatural problems she wants to solve?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Furthermore, two of her aspirations must relate to her mundane life, or
 at least the mundane world.
 Does she have friends she made a promise to? Does she have an internet
 community to run? What is her school life like, and is there something
 she would especially like to accomplish there?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some of your Aspirations should be short term goals that can be completed
 in a session or two, and at least one should be a longer-term goal that
 may take a whole Chapter to complete.
 Aspirations are one of the main ways you earn beats, which advance your
 character.
 They help the Storyteller know where you want to go with your character,
 and what kinds of stories you want them to experience.
\end_layout

