 When a Luminous Blossoms, the first part of the world she changes is herself.
 In her nascent Dreamscape, she weaves an image of her world into her very
 soul.
 While she doesn't truly lose her mortal Virtues and Vices, they no longer
 anchor her well enough against her own dreams, nor the world's pressures.
 Rather, she learns to draw on that image of a better world, and the means
 by which she knows she can touch the world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Her vision of her ideal world is called her Dream.
 It is the one possible future out of endless possibilities that she considers
 truly her own, one she could comfortably live in for herself and those
 she loves.
 A Hopeful who Dreams of "Among the Stars" may draw on the magic of Muirias,
 but that world is ultimately a kind of compromise.
 Unfettered by such things, they would dream of a world where all have a
 place among the countless stars, each planet holding its own form of utopia.
 When a Luminous takes a risk to make their Dream a reality, she regains
 one Willpower.
 When a Luminous makes noticeable progress in realizing that Dream for herself
 or the broader world, she regains all Willpower.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The means by which she knows she can change the world is called her Will.
 Even if she has many talents, it is the one she holds closest to her heart,
 the thing she falls back on when everything else fails.
 A Dreamer who writes for a newspaper in her waking life may have a Will
 of a 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
