The Hopeful draw on the external world, as much as they rely on their inner
 strength.
 Nobody can just fight their whole life without...
 something breaking inside.
 Not alone, not without something to hold themselves steady.
 A Touchstone is something or someone tangible that gives the Luminous emotional
 strength, and reminds her that there is good in the world even now.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sometimes, those remainders are the people she have helped in life and now
 walk by her side.
 Sometimes, it's her family of choice and close friends who once rescued
 her from her own darkest times.
 Sometimes, it is the beautiful gardens that remind her of the wonder the
 world has always had.
 Whatever form it takes, a Luminous' Touchstones are the things the Luminous
 can draw on for emotional strength even in the darkest times.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, their Touchstones represent vulnerabilities in her life as much
 as they are a source of strength.
 When a Luminous permanently loses one of her Touchstones, she takes a five-dice
 severe Hope attack.
 Whenever a Luminous acts to defend one of her Touchstones, she regains
 a Willpower point.
 If this defense causes her serious harm, she regains all her spent Willpower
 points.
 
\end_layout

