\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The three different power categories makes it easier for me to formalize
 different mechanics and roles for each.
 From a design perspective, the difference is this:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Regalia are equipment and passive effects that improve the Luminous.
 They are the closest a Luminous has to passive abilities, that make them
 better by just having them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Domains are things that shape the world directly, in freeform ways more
 like Influences than anything else.
 They are used often, but are still active, not passive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Charms are powerful but narrower abilities that give the Luminous things
 that feel like powerful 
\begin_inset Quotes xld
\end_inset

spells
\begin_inset Quotes xrd
\end_inset

.
 They are the most active of their powers, requiring very explicit casting.
\end_layout

