\begin_layout Section
Shining Heart
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Far too often, Luminous find themselves wanting to change the world when
 they personally experience the cruelties of the world.
 They cannot help but feel the pains of those around them, and even if they
 escape the worst of it personally, they almost certainly grow close to
 someone who suffers from it for one reason or another.
 They are themselves hurt by a world that tells them they are naive to hope,
 and a thousand times again when they see the pain reflected in another.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Sensitivity 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Sensitivity|(textbf
\end_layout

\end_inset

 A Luminous' strong emotions combined with their natural concern for others
 meld together into a deep empathy they call "Sensitivity", only growing
 stronger from their magic to connect hearts.
 Sensitivity is a dice pool equal to half the Hopeful's Reverie rounded
 up.
 Merits and other abilities may add additional dice to this pool, and non-Lumino
us may gain Sensitivity dice through merits or other traits.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The kind of strong empathy that Sensitivity reflects isn't just an magical
 ailment/drawback as Princess' writing implies.
 It's what makes them Blossom in the first place.
 I've kept this mechanic because it's so appropriate to the core of what
 magical girls do.
 The mundane merit version of it is to try and reinforce this point.
 All of a Luminous' supernatural empathy is their Echo, not Sensitivity.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Take their Hand 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As much as the pains of others hurt them too, the Luminous can at least
 put it to good use.
 The level of connection they can have makes it easier for them to comfort
 and understand others.
 Sensitivity provides the following bonuses:
\end_layout

