To the Luminous, walking by putting one foot in front of the other feels
 the same as simply imagining moving forward.
 There is no hard line between jumping onto their bed, or imagining an gravity
 defying leap between roofs.
 Luminous are caught between dreams and reality in their Dream Form, and
 they may draw on that to touch the world in all the ways they could in
 a dream.
 Whether they move or only imagine doing so, it still happens.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a Luminous acts upon the world through imagination and thought, she
 performs a Weaving Action.
 Instead of rolling a dice pool using a normal skill, she uses a different
 set of eight Weaving Skills.
 Weaving is as natural to a Luminous as any other action, and thus has no
 cost.
 As such, they may reflexively roll any dice pool as a Weaving Action, even
 when contesting rolls or for rolls caused by hostile magic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While Weaving isn't blatantly supernatural, the surreal ways it touches
 the world are still not subtle.
 A Luminous defies gravity, the motion of her feet doesn't quite line up
 with how fast she moves, and many other little inconsistencies.
 Any witnesses may roll Perception to notice the nonphysical nature of her
 actions.
