\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Interactions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Beasts see themselves as kin to all supernatural beings.
 As much as they are rooted in humanity's history, the Luminous and Maou
 are still supernatural.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Kinship
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Maou and Luminous both have the same Kinship with Beasts as the Awakened.
 However, a Luminous' Mundane Form veils this fact – she has no Kinship
 with Beasts in Mundane Form.
 Due to their stronger connection with the mundane, Thicker Than Water does
 not affect the Luminous.
 However, if a Beast applies the Family Ties condition, it applies even
 in a Luminous' Mundane Form.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Passing Resemblance has little use with the Luminous or the Maou.
 They do not have means to recognize each other passively, instead using
 their powers to reveal their nature to others.
 At best, a Beast can pass for a transformed Luminous by faking the dissonance
 with physics that Weaving Actions can cause.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Flex Commentary
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
There's no fluff reason Luminous should ignore Thicker Than Water; this
 is more a mechanical fix.
 Social Maneuvering gets 
\emph on
